Date:  12/11/1902
Source:  Otago Witness
Author:
Vol / Page:  74
Edition:
Quote:  The fleece-picker takes the fleece by the hind legs, and gathers it towards him; takes it to the rolling table, and throws it out with the outside of the flecce upwards; the roller skirts it, rolls it up tightly, and hands it to the classer, who puts the fleece in the proper bin.
Notes:

Date:  0/0/1913
Source:  Country Work
Author:  CARR
Vol / Page:  14
Edition:
Quote:  Fleece-picking. - As soon as a shearer has taken the fleece off and let the sheep go through the port-hole to the counting-out pen, the picker gathers the fleece up in such a manner that she or he can on getting to the rolling table, throw it out with the breech part at the right end.
